Abuja – The National Judicial Council (NJC) on Monday issued fresh query to the embattled Chief Justice of Nigeria, Justice Walter Onnoghen. It had reconvened on Monday in an emergency meeting to consider the responses of Justice Onnoghen and Justice Muhammad, acting Chief Justice of Nigeria, to the three petitions written against them. But after deliberations, members of the apex judicial body resolved to constitute a Preliminary Complaints Assessment Committee in accordance with Regulation 17 of the National Judicial Council Judicial Discipline Regulations 2017 and report to council on February 13, 2019. Director of Information, NJC, Soji Oye, confirmed in a statement that the council would reconvene on Wednesday, February 13, 2019, for further deliberation on the issue. The NJC spokesperson added: “Council also received a new petition written by the Economic and Financial Crimes Commission (EFCC) against Hon. Mr. Justice W.S.N. Onnoghen, GCON and forwarded it to him for his response within seven working days.” Meanwhile, the NJC has reaffirmed its confidence in Justice Umaru Abdullahi’s interim headship of the apex judicial body.